Fig. 1A
 depicts the FE-SEM images of keratin/PVA hydrogels containing different amount of C-dots. As in the figure, the keratin/PVA hydrogel (containing 0% C-dots) shows the network structure formed by several fibrous like structures arranged without specific direction. The adjacent polymer chains were joined under the EBI treatment and a 3D network was formed [5]. The morphology of the hydrogel was found to be changed after the addition of C-dots. As compared to the C-dots free hydrogel, the hydrogels with C-dots possess more fibrous morphology. A good fibrous structure was obtained at low content of C-dots whereas higher content of C-dots led to the less porosity and less fibrous structure. As compared to the other hydrogels, the keratin/PVA/C-0.05 hydrogel showed the best porous structure with 3D hydrogel networks (Fig. 1B
).
